result.execSummary:
Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Daniel G Krajewski in court with attorney Terry L. Nussberger.  James Jay Rennicke appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Heard along with 16CF8.  DE/Atty will waive PH.  Court instructs on waiver of PH, court will accept waiver.  Information filed this day in court by the State.  Will proceed to arraignment in both cases.  Waive reading of the information, enter plea of NG to all counts. Set for plea/sentencing 4-05-16 @ 2:00PM.  Bond continues.

Defendant Daniel G Krajewski in court with attorney Terry L. Nussberger.  Defendant Daniel G Krajewski in custody.  James Jay Rennicke appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Heard along with 15CF194.    Waive formal reading of the CC.  DE/Atty will waive time limits for PH, court instructs on waiver of time limits.  Court will accept waiver of time limits.  Set for 2-23-16 @ 1:00PM, PH.  Atty wishes to address the issue of bond.  $1000.00 cash, must be supervised by parents, brother Andrew will be allowed to superviser, no access to electronic devices of any kind.  Bonds will be concurrent.

BOND CLARIFICATION FROM JA - PER JUDGE ANDERSON - BOND IS TO BE $500 CASH BOND ON 15CF194 AND $500 CASH BOND ON 16CF8 FOR A TOTAL OF $1,000.00 CASH FOR BOTH CASES.  BOTH BONDS TO RUN CONCURRENT WITH CONDITIONS.  THIS IS TO CLARIFY THE COURT MINUTES FROM THE 1/19/16 HEARING.  LY

Must be supervised by parents, brother Andrew will be allowed to supervise, but no discussion of the case.  No access to electronic devices of any kind.  No contact with T.D.K. dob 1/7/2000.  No contact with Stacey Krajewski.  No contact with juvenile females.  Bonds will be concurrent.
